io.github.nucleuspowered.nucleus.api.text

Interface NucleusTextTemplate

  • All Superinterfaces:
    TextElement, TextRepresentable

    public interface NucleusTextTemplate
extends TextRepresentable
    Represents a wrapped TextTemplate that Nucleus uses to create texts from templates.

      • getForCommandSource

        Text getForCommandSource(CommandSource source,
                         @Nullable
                         Map<String,Function<CommandSource,Optional<Text>>> tokensArray,
                         @Nullable
                         Map<String,Object> variables)
        Gets the Text where the tokens have been parsed from the viewpoint of the supplied CommandSource.

        By supplying a token array, these token identifiers act as additional tokens that could be encountered, and will be used above standard tokens. This is useful for having a token in a specific context, such as "displayfrom", which might only be used in a message, and is not worth registering in a NucleusMessageTokenService.TokenParser. They must not contain the token start or end delimiters.

        The variables are items that might be used by tokens, and is generally best used with your own messages and tokens. NucleusMessageTokenService.TokenParsers are passed this map.

        Parameters:
        source - The CommandSource that will influence what is displayed by the tokens.
        tokensArray - The extra tokens that can be used to parse a text.
        variables - The variables.
        Returns:
        The parsed Text
